Mines_End().details: function to end player current game and receive payout

Mines_GetMaxReveal().details: function to view the max number of tiles to reveal in mines

returns.maxReveal: array with max number of tiles to reveal for each number of mines

Mines_GetMultipliers(uint256,uint256).details: function to view the current mines multipliers

params.numMines: number of mines in the game

returns.multiplier: multiplier of selected numMines and numRevealed

Mines_GetState(address).details: get current game state of player

params.player: address of the player that made the bet

Mines_Refund().details: Function to get refund for game if VRF request fails

Mines_Reveal(bool[25],bool).details: function to reveal tiles in an ongoing game

params.isCashout: if true and player doesn't reveal mines, will cashout
params.tiles: array of tiles that the player wishes to reveal, can't choose already revealed tiles, true equals that tile will be revealed

params.numMines: number of mines to set multipliers for

Mines_Start(uint256,address,uint8,bool[2.details: function to start mines game, player cannot currently be in a game

params.isCashout: if true, game will give payout if player doesn't reveal mines
params.numMines: number of mines present in game, range from 1-24
